{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bdd13cb6-9620-4f45-bafd-c1c57f8ba17b","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_snQkFiQuMrXKzwOzDtSg7V","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Explaining .NET 10 upgrades"},"type":"function"}],"interactionId":"a46adde8-b601-429a-b28a-9e396cf7e271","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about issues they'll encounter when upgrading a .NET 9 class library to .NET 10. Let me address each of the five points they've raised, based on my knowledge of .NET 10 breaking changes and new features.\n\n1. **[InlineArray(16)] struct with explicit [StructLayout(LayoutKind.Explicit, Size = 64)]** - In .NET 10, there's a breaking change where inline arrays now must not have explicit layout attributes. The runtime will throw a `TypeLoadException` if an inline array has `[StructLayout(LayoutKind.Explicit)]`. The fix is to remove the explicit `StructLayout` attribute and let the runtime handle the layout.\n\n\n2. **DriveInfo.DriveFormat on Linux** - In .NET 10, the behavior changed so that `DriveInfo.DriveFormat` now returns the actual filesystem type (like \"ext4\", \"xfs\", \"tmpfs\") instead of the mount source path it was returning before. Any code that was relying on the old incorrect values will need to be updated to work with the actual filesystem type strings.\n\n3. **NU1510 warnings about pruned references** - .NET 10 introduced automatic dependency pruning that removes unused transitive dependencies, which can trigger NU1510 warnings. To fix this, either explicitly add `PackageReference` entries for packages you need, or disable pruning entirely with `<EnablePackagePruning>false</EnablePackagePruning>` in the project file.\n\n4. **Transitive NuGet dependencies not audited for vulnerabilities** - In .NET 10, NuGet audit now checks transitive dependencies by default instead of just direct ones, since `NuGetAuditMode` changed from `direct` to `all`. This means vulnerability warnings will surface for transitive packages, and you'll need to update them to safe versions, pin specific versions, or suppress particular advisories.\n\n5. **FilePatternMatch.Stem null check** - The `Stem` property now returns `string.Empty` instead of `null` when there's no stem, so existing null checks will never trigger. I need to update those checks to use `string.IsNullOrEmpty` instead.\n\nLet me pull together a comprehensive summary of all five breaking changes.","outputTokens":821,"requestId":"C420:74DAE:1F464FE:2355066:6A07D00B"},"id":"8e24d2b0-46d1-45ac-b141-d7b7b4680ec1","timestamp":"2026-05-16T02:02:04.848Z","parentId":"7d61a719-fef1-41f0-9cfc-e8df025a08a3"}
