{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"333fb966-03d0-4c47-b8bc-cb81806ff7a7","content":"Here are the five issues and fixes for your .NET 9 → 10 upgrade:\n\n**1. InlineArray + explicit StructLayout → `TypeLoadException`**\n.NET 10 disallows explicit layout on inline arrays. Remove `[StructLayout(LayoutKind.Explicit, Size = 64)]` — the runtime now controls layout. If you need a specific size, ensure the element type × length gives the correct size.\n\n**2. `DriveInfo.DriveFormat` on Linux**\n.NET 10 now returns the actual filesystem type (e.g. `\"ext4\"`, `\"tmpfs\"`, `\"xfs\"`) instead of the previous incorrect values. Update your string comparisons to match the real kernel filesystem type names.\n\n**3. NU1510 — pruned package references**\n.NET 10 enables package dependency pruning by default. Unused transitive references are removed, triggering NU1510. Either:\n- Add explicit `<PackageReference>` for packages you actually use, or\n- Set `<EnablePackagePruning>false</EnablePackagePruning>` in your project to opt out.\n\n**4. Transitive NuGet audit warnings**\n`NuGetAuditMode` now defaults to `all` (was `direct`). You'll see vulnerability warnings for transitive packages. Fix by updating vulnerable packages, pinning safe versions via `<PackageVersion>`, or suppressing specific advisories with `<NuGetAuditSuppress>`.\n\n**5. `FilePatternMatch.Stem` null check**\n`Stem` now returns `string.Empty` instead of `null` when there's no stem. Replace:\n```csharp\nif (match.Stem == null)\n```\nwith:\n```csharp\nif (string.IsNullOrEmpty(match.Stem))\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a46adde8-b601-429a-b28a-9e396cf7e271","outputTokens":434,"requestId":"C426:1EBA3E:1DF4BCD:21FCA9F:6A07D01B"},"id":"2d4512dd-54e6-437f-87b6-4260b0bf094b","timestamp":"2026-05-16T02:02:12.655Z","parentId":"494f71a7-6a1b-422b-a9ab-8caa39332237"}
